text:
今年端午節剛好在美國, 我決定跟大自然過. 我站在加州紅木樹旁邊看起來超級小, 就是因為它超越1400年!!
看到這麼美麗的森林讓我覺的我們真的要照顧好我們的地球. 幾千年的努力, 我們幾十年就要破壞了. 希望我們可以越來越好 記得環保 多照顧我們的地球.
After visiting the redwood forest for the first time it really got me thinking
about climate change and how our daily choices play such a huge role in nature.
It took nature over a thousand years to give us these magestic trees, let's not
destroy in a couple of decades. I hope that people can realize that everyone can
help no matter how small the action. 
📸 @meaghan_kimbrell @ Armstrong Redwoods State Natural Reserve
